# OmniRoute v3.8.34 â€” 100-PR Engineering Roadmap

> **Project**: OmniRoute â€” Unified AI router (160+ providers, OpenAI-compatible, RTK/Caveman compression, auto-fallback, MCP/A2A, Desktop + PWA, Electron)
> **Author**: KooshaPari
> **Date**: 2026-06-23
> **Target version**: v3.8.34 â†’ v4.0.0
> **Status**: Draft, awaiting triage

---

## 0. Executive Summary

This roadmap defines **100 substantial pull requests** (each â‰Ą500 lines of code, documentation, tests, and fixtures) that move OmniRoute from "open-source proxy" to "production-grade AI routing platform". They are organised into **eight themes** matching user-visible capability areas, derived from:

1. **Live community pain points** in [`diegosouzapw/OmniRoute/issues`](https://github.com/diegosouzapw/OmniRoute/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen) (53 open issues, 1.2k forks, 6.8k stars).
2. The current upstream architecture in `OmniRoute-upstream/` â€” 66 provider executors under `open-sse/executors/`, the `(dashboard)` Next.js 16 app under `src/app/`, domain layer in `src/domain/`, libraries in `src/lib/`, shared contracts in `src/shared/`.
3. **Open issues directly informing PRs** (cross-referenced in each entry): #4806 quota model listing regression, #4802 / #4602 Codex WebSocket stream serialization, #4795 catastrophic backtracking, #4771 / #4623 OOM/heap exhaustion, #4714 Claude tool-message regression, #4683 Qoder jobToken handshake, #4665 model self-id mismatch, #4608 Aliyun WAF, #4603 provider UID vs display name, #4599/#4441 release build hygiene, #4436 dashboard bundle bloat, #4329 `:free` suffix for auto combos, #4295/#4294 Cursor/Antigravity MITM, #4268 Stacked RTK/Caveman, #4262 prompt-cache/usage reporting, #4252 Undici 502 bursts.

### Legend

- **S** = â‰¤1k LOC, 1-3 days
- **M** = 1-3k LOC, 1 week
- **L** = 3-6k LOC, 2 weeks
- **XL** = >6k LOC, 3+ weeks
- **Risk**: Low / Med / High â€” based on blast radius and how many providers touch the change.

